Mr. May has a very strong infantry combat background as he was a squad leader during Operation: Moshtarak and was tasked with controlling key parts of the city, training the soldiers of the Afghanistan National Army and Afghanistan National Police, as well as fighting against a well-trained enemy in their own back yard. It features a three position selector - Mode 1 for Safe, Mode 2 for traditional semi-automatic Mode, or Mode 3 for Binary Mode. In Binary Mode, the firearm will discharge one round with every function of the trigger, whether a pull or a release. A user can negate the round that would otherwise be fired during the release function by moving the selector back to Mode 2 and then safely releasing the trigger.
